Description: Upper body sherd of Chian pottery oinochoe; white slip; exterior: glazed black (fired red); inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: The number in Petrie's catalogue, 261, is written in ink on the exterior surface of the sherd. For parallels, see 1886,0401.508.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 261)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 665, no. 222)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0046) (phase 2)
